{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778518117,"nonce":"19vkzHk48ZmY/5MaEYQgihrZMJU=","message":"## Final design decisions for the reorg\n\nCapturing decisions made through the design discussion so implementation can proceed:\n\n### Layout: flat-by-hash, no grandfathering\n\n- Each top-level results/ dir is `results/\u003c7-char-issue-hash\u003e/` — the issue is the atomic unit.\n- No phase-level parent dirs in the directory tree. Phase membership is README metadata, not hierarchy.\n- **`results/part2_5/` does NOT get grandfathered.** Earlier subagent suggested it; rejected — leaving a legacy nested island defeats the point. part2_5 contents migrate to flat-by-hash with everything else.\n- Cloud-provider subdirs (`runpod/`, `modal/`, etc.) disappear entirely. They were never meaningful per CLAUDE.md.\n\n### Inside each `\u003chash\u003e/`\n\n```\n\u003chash\u003e/\n├── README.md                      one paragraph orienting context\n├── RUN_PLAN.md                    if the work involves training runs\n├── notes/\u003ctopic\u003e.md               narrative + analysis writeups\n├── figures/\u003ctopic\u003e/spec.json      figure specs\n└── runs/\u003cvariant\u003e.json            per-run hyperparameters (flat, not nested)\n```\n\n### Run-folder convention\n\n- **`runs/\u003cvariant\u003e.json`** flat — one JSON file per run, not a directory with a single file in it.\n- For complex sweeps where variant names would balloon (~50+ chars), use `runs/\u003chash\u003e.json` + `runs_index.json` mapping hash → human label + params.\n- Promote a run to `runs/\u003cvariant\u003e/` directory only if it accrues additional per-run files (notes, debug artifacts). Lazy promotion.\n\n### Orphan archaeology (11 unspecd `_artifacts/` runs)\n\n- Reconstruct `run.json` for each from chat logs / git history / `meta.json` / training logs.\n- Each reconstructed `run.json` carries a `reconstructed: true` field + a \"Reconstructed\" preamble in README noting source confidence: \"CLI flags, timing, and tracking issue were inferred from \u003csources\u003e. Marked uncertain where reconstruction was incomplete: \u003clist\u003e.\"\n- If reconstruction fails completely for a given run, archive under `_artifacts/_orphan/` with a stub README.\n\n### Bundling with symlink rollout (`0f1af24`)\n\n- Single feature branch, two commits: (1) reorg layout, (2) figure-save call-site migration to the new feedbax API (after `67bf476` merges).\n- Implementation uses the new `feedbax.plot.save_figure(package, experiment, topic)` API — the symlink is automatic per the project routing config.\n\n### Out of scope (separately tracked)\n\n- **`1_general.assets/` and `2_general.assets/` PNG strip** — `e75ddd7` (important + release, deferred).\n- **Notebook .md files** that embed those PNGs — out of scope; they keep their image references which will resolve via symlinks after the dual-tree migration.\n\n### Cross-refs\n\n- feedbax `67bf476` — figure-save API design + implementation (prerequisite for call-site migration here).\n- `0f1af24` — symlink mirror-tree (bundled into this work).\n- `e75ddd7` — asset PNG history strip (deferred, separate).\n- `fdad09d` — `train_minimax.py` auto-write `run.json` (separate, post-reorg this becomes easier).","files":null}]}